
# 🧰 Install Jenkins on RHEL / Rocky (Final Working Guide)

## 1️⃣ Install Java (required)

```bash
sudo yum install -y fontconfig java-21-openjdk
java -version
```

✔ Confirm Java 21 is installed

---

## 2️⃣ Add Jenkins repository (using curl ✅)

```bash
sudo curl -L -o /etc/yum.repos.d/jenkins.repo \
https://pkg.jenkins.io/rpm-stable/jenkins.repo
```

---

## 3️⃣ Add GPG key (correct + working)

```bash
sudo rpm --import https://pkg.jenkins.io/rpm-stable/jenkins.io.key
```

👉 If needed (safe fallback):

```bash
sudo curl -L -o /tmp/jenkins.key https://pkg.jenkins.io/rpm-stable/jenkins.io.key
sudo rpm --import /tmp/jenkins.key
```

---

## 4️⃣ Clean yum cache

```bash
sudo yum clean all
```

---

## 5️⃣ Install Jenkins

```bash
sudo yum install -y jenkins
```

✔ Now it should install without errors

---

## 6️⃣ Start Jenkins service

```bash
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl start jenkins
sudo systemctl enable jenkins
```

---

## 7️⃣ Check status

```bash
sudo systemctl status jenkins
```

✔ Look for:

```
active (running)
```

---

## 8️⃣ Open firewall (important in RHEL)

```bash
sudo firewall-cmd --permanent --add-port=8080/tcp
sudo firewall-cmd --reload
```

---

## 9️⃣ Access Jenkins

```
http://<your-server-ip>:8080
```

---

## 🔐 10️⃣ Unlock Jenkins

```bash
sudo cat /var/lib/jenkins/secrets/initialAdminPassword
```